snippet.textDisplay:
Maybe let's make a thread in the comments for the Try Guys to read about people who completely ignore quarantine. It could be funny stories or not. I think if the Try Guys read them, they can be based on them warn people and raise awareness even more. My story:
When I was walking my dog through a park (keeping distance, obviously) I saw kids playing on the playground, which had a huge sign that prohibited using playgrounds. The kids were mature enough to be able to read (looked around 10-12 y.o) so I told them not to play there. Them their mother started screaming at me that she was supervising her children (apparently, watching them from almost half a mile is "supervising") and how dare I scream at them (I did NOT) and that the coronavirus is not going to spread by playing. At that point, I just knew how I'm going to react. I said " I'm sorry ma'am, but you're acting really irresponsi.." and I fake sneezed at that point. I was close enough for it to scare her as she got close to me. Without saying any more, I left, leaving that woman pale as a wall, scrubbing her face and hands rigorously with a shitty hand sanitizer you can buy in any supermarket for like 25 cents.
